<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id52a243f0-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s1339"><num value="1339">§ 1339.</num><heading> Postal matters</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The district courts shall have original jurisdiction of any civil action arising under any Act of Congress relating to the postal service.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id52a243f1-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/932">62 Stat. 932</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id52a243f2-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id52a243f3-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 41(6) (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s24">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 24</ref>, par. 6, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1092">36 Stat. 1092</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Changes were made in phraseology.</p>
</note>
